The paper discusses optimizing the performance of analytical database engines through multi-dimensional indexing, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The use of machine learning techniques to optimize the index structure and data storage suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves scanning and filtering operations, which are common in data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
